The paper deals with private information retrieval (PIR), which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It specifically focuses on multi-server single-message PIR, which involves multiple servers and a single message, making it relevant to distributed computing (cs.DC). The presence of side information also brings in the aspect of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also involves coding schemes, which is a topic in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the use of side information can be seen as a form of machine learning or information retrieval (cs.SI).
